There are no plans to expand this class. The general rule is 10% of students will drop a class so being 9th on the wait list might be pushing it.

This is the first semester that both EE120 and EE105 have filled up! With the new 16 series, the upper div EE classes are gaining popularity so it's not easy to predict which phase you should sign up for EE classes anymore.

children.subject: It looks like the current room for the class, 150 GSPP, only seats 86, so it's probably a space issue. So unless they're able to change the room for the class (which again seems unlikely), I doubt they'll expand the class.

Each class has a budget and that is how enrollment limits are determined. This class typically has 3 REC sections from which to choose. The 8AM section is not popular, which is why the sections are so uneven; however the instructor may want students to move so they are more balanced.

But it seems unfair that the classes will not expand to account for the output of the EE16 series. These students will now want to take upper division EE courses, so these must be expanded to account for this increase. Many of us would like to take an EE class, but were told Phase 2'ing these was 'very safe' by an Engineering advisor.

Why are there no plans to expand this class? There are no labs and more than enough section capacity to accommodate an increased class size. I don't understand why the department is trying to increase interest in EE when they cap a class like this at double digits, especially when the class size was 120 seats last semester

history.content: Back in phase 1, people were saying EE120 would be a "phase 2" class. There are 8 people out of 50 on the waitlist right now for a class of 80. Is this class size of 80 fixed (no expansion), and if so, what are the chances of getting in. Two out of three discussion sections are still open. (32/40 and 1/40 filled...)
